latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Are you more afraid of success than failure?⁣
⁣
It’s okay, most people are⁣
⁣
In this video I talk about the most important thing to help you get over that ⁣
⁣
When you are…⁣
⁣
Broke⁣
Overweight⁣
Sad⁣
Struggling in life⁣
⁣
Most people will help lift you up⁣
⁣
But when you start to win…⁣
⁣
Get into elite shape⁣
Make a lot of money⁣
Have great relationships⁣
Happy⁣
⁣
That’s when some people will try to pull you down⁣
⁣
A lot of people don’t have the mental toughness to handle that and then sabotage their success and progress because of it⁣
⁣
This one tip might help⁣
⁣
Also, I was speaking with a new client today about how she wanted to lose weight to be more confident showing up on video because she’s in real estate⁣
⁣
I told her I understood and that makes sense as showing up on video helps people get to know you much better⁣
⁣
Then I started feeling shitty about myself telling her that and not showing up in more videos myself so plan on doing more of these if that’s okay with ya⁣
⁣
It’s also much easier to flip the camera on and talk versus photos because I have tendency to not be a big photo guy ⁣
⁣
When in a situation where a photo seems appropriate I tend to go with taking a mental photo of the moment versus an actual one so yeah

If you want to be next and tired of wasting time, energy, and money on things that don’t work after being stuck for quite some time simply shoot me a message saying “Results” and we will see if our coaching program would be a fit 🚀  Taking the first step is always the hardest but it’s what this client did in reaching out and her life is now changed forever ❤️

Many new followers recently so thought be good to share about who I am 🤷‍♂️⁣
⁣
My legal first name is Bowen, my grandmas maiden name, but have always went by Bo for short⁣
⁣
I am from a small town of 800 people in Iowa, Janesville, and graduated with 22 kids, would not change it for anything⁣
⁣
I’ve broken my back, my foot, tore my acl and meniscus, tore my labrum in my shoulder twice, broke my collar bone, and worst was breaking my leg requiring two surgeries. You learn a lot by sitting on the sideline not able to compete with your friends⁣
⁣
I was held back in pre-school because every time my mom or grandma dropped me off I would start crying and throwing a fit so wasn’t emotional read for kindergarten⁣
⁣
I am allergic to dogs which sucks because I love dogs, puffy eyes and face are always worth the pet⁣
⁣
I played 4 sports in high school - baseball, football, basketball, and ran track⁣
⁣
Was all-state in baseball, football, and basketball, and placed 1st in conference in the long jump⁣
⁣
Got offers to play 3 different sports in college but chose baseball which was always my first love⁣
⁣
I’ve lived in Minneapolis, Chicago, LA, kinda Ireland and Omaha currently but have no idea where I’ll plant a flag at this point long-term⁣
⁣
For the last 18 months or so I’ve lived out of a suitcase and only spent a few months at “home” in total⁣
⁣
I have symmetry ocd, meaning if their is dust on the tv I can’t focus until I wipe the tv off lol⁣
⁣
I think am funny, and a goal of mine in my life is to perform stand up comedy once before I die - before I left Chicago I signed up for improv classes at Second City⁣
⁣
I hate spiders and snakes⁣
⁣
I think you can always learn from everyone, doesn’t matter if that’s having dinner across from Warren Buffet or a homeless person on the street⁣
⁣
Good Will Hunting is my favorite movie of all time with Dumb & Dumber being a close 2nd⁣
⁣
Believe journaling is underrated especially by men, huge power in getting your thoughts out of your head and onto paper⁣
⁣
You will never regret in your life making your health and fitness a priority, pinky promise ya⁣
⁣
That’s all the length I have for words, cheers 🥃

latestPosts.caption:
What if I told you within the next week I wanted to be married?

For context I am currently single as pringle

Do you think that would be a good idea?

Probably not right

The chances of me finding my person in the next week whom I want to spend the rest of my life is very low

Even if I found someone in the next week it probably wouldn’t be a good fit for thousands of different reasons right?

You would more than likely call it a very dumb idea

What if I told you in the next 5 years I would like to be married?

You would probably say okay that’s much better

It gives you more time to go on dates, get focused on your ideal partner, and know what type of woman you are looking for

You would probably think that’s not a bad goal yeah?

Nobody does that with their health and fitness

Everyone is trying to be married next week

I have to drop 30lbs before this vacation in 6 weeks

I have a wedding coming up and need to drop 15lbs in a few weeks to fit into this dress

We are getting family photos in a month and would really like to drop 20lbs

I look at this the same way you would look at me if I told you I want to be married by end of next week...

This sabotages so many long term because even if you hit your short term goal you do it as a sacrifice to what is best for you long term

You do a quick fix, starve yourself, or something extreme that you can’t sustain for very long

REAL CHANGE, like we focus on with the woman in our program takes time

It takes time to change your daily and weekly habits, consistency, actions, behaviors, mindset, and education around what works for you

It’s the ONLY path because it ultimately leads to long term success and much higher likelihood of actually being able to sustain those results

#fitness #health #weightloss

It’s just part of the process

Confident, powerful, unstoppable transformation

latestPosts.caption:
What have you all tried over the years?

We ask this question to hundreds of struggling women every single day and their answers are all very simliar

…6 week challenges…$250
…detox tea from a friend who joined an MLM…$300
…few personal trainers who spent most of the session not their phone…$2000
…group fitness…$150 a month
…Crossfit…$175 a month
…hormone supplements…$1000
…meal delivery services…$500
…supplements…$75 per month
…apps on your phone…$30 per month

I understand at first blush that number might seem absurd and you think, “No way!” 

But when you start breaking it down everything adds up overtime and it adds up to be a lot especially when at the end you are still frustrated spinning your wheels making no real progress right?

Then after a woman lists out all the things she’s tried we will ask if they have ever worked 1-1 with someone before and they often say “No too expensive” 🤔

Many things in fitness miss the mark

They focus on the external, not the internal

We first focus on changing the woman within first then the external changes she desires will come over time as a by product of that

No pill will make up for poor lifestyle choices

When that’s successful our mission is simple

When a woman joins our program and works with us for a period of time it will be the last serious investment she will ever make in a fitness program 💯

She will walk away feeling confident and empowered that she can go off to sustain the results on her own and never have to spend time, energy, money, or effort on something else ever again 💪🏻

#fitness #health #mindset #weightlosshelp

latestPosts.caption:
How long will you continue to reach for motivation?

Have you ever found it? 
If you did how long did it last?

A day? Few days? Few weeks?  That’s usually how it goes

Big difference between those who struggle with their weight and those who are in great shape is how they view motivation

Fit people don’t really think of it much

Working out, eating right, moving their body has become a part of their lifestyle and just something they have done consistently for a long time

Unfit people tend to focus on motivation

They think just one day suddenly will get hit with it and then they will use motivation the rest of their life to get into shape

That will never happen

Many women never lose weight or get into great shape because they have waited months, years, and decades for sustainable motivation, and the problem is it will never come 💯

#fitness #health #weightloss #weightlossjourney #transformation
